        "en": "Related substances—Conduct this procedure using light-resistant vessels. To a quantity of Pitavastatin Calcium Orally Disintegrating Tablets, equivalent to 20 mg of mL of the standard solution under the above operating con- ditions, the internal standard and pitavastatin are eluted in pitavastatin calcium (C50H46 CaF2N2O8), add 60 mL of a mix- this order with the resolution between these peaks being not less than 8. System repeatability: When the test is repeated 6 times with 10 mL of the standard solution under the above operat-ing conditions, the relative standard deviation of the ratio of the peak area of pitavastatin to that of the internal standard is not more than 1.0z."
